            "id": "devotion",
            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EPaul%20taught%20Timothy%20three%20vital%20truths%20about%20finances.%20First%2C%20he%20taught%20him%20that%20the%20love%20of%20money%20can%20be%20dangerous%20to%20one's%20spiritual%20health.%20Money%20itself%20is%20not%20evil%2C%20but%20the%20love%20of%20money%20is%20a%20dangerous%20deception%20that%20can%20lead%20even%20to%20being%20drawn%20away%20from%20the%20faith.%20The%20proper%20attitude%20toward%20money%20must%20be%20one%20of%20contentment.%20As%20we%20live%20our%20lives%2C%20we%20must%20be%20thankful%20for%20what%20we%20have%2C%20not%20always%20wanting%20what%20we%20don't%20have.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20second%20truth%20is%20that%20God%20desires%20to%20bless%20us.%20He%20%22richly%20gives%20us%20all%20we%20need%20for%20our%20enjoyment%22%20(1%20Timothy%206%3A17).%20God%20is%20not%20a%20taker-%20He's%20a%20giver!%20He%20longs%20to%20bless%20us%20for%20our%20enjoyment.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20third%20truth%20Paul%20shared%20regarding%20money%20is%20the%20principle%20of%20giving.%20He%20urged%20Timothy%20to%20instruct%20the%20rich%20to%20remember%20to%20use%20their%20earthly%20wealth%20for%20doing%20good%2C%20thus%20laying%20up%20an%20eternal%20reward%20in%20heaven%20(vv.%2018-19).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20finances%20we%20invest%20in%20others%20and%20in%20God's%20work%20will%20be%20multiplied%20back%20to%20us%20in%20the%20life%20to%20come.%20Let's%20use%20our%20money%20as%20a%20tool%20for%20eternal%20investment%2C%20and%20one%20day%20we%20will%20see%20it%20again.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
        {
