            "title": "Old Testament Reading",
            "api_nlt_to_ref": "Jeremiah.37:1-38:28",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3EJeremiah%2037%3A1-38%3A28%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_37_1%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2237%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3EJeremiah%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E37%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EZedekiah%20Calls%20for%20Jeremiah%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EZedekiah%20son%20of%20Josiah%20succeeded%20Jehoiachin%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E37%3A1a%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3EConiah%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20a%20variant%20spelling%20of%20Jehoiachin.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20son%20of%20Jehoiakim%20as%20the%20king%20of%20Judah.%20He%20was%20appointed%20by%20King%20Nebuchadnezzar%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E37%3A1b%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3ENebuchadrezzar%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20a%20variant%20spelling%20of%20Nebuchadnezzar.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20of%20Babylon.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_37_2%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2237%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20neither%20King%20Zedekiah%20nor%20his%20attendants%20nor%20the%20people%20who%20were%20left%20in%20the%20land%20listened%20to%20what%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20said%20through%20Jeremiah.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_37_3%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2237%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3ENevertheless%2C%20King%20Zedekiah%20sent%20Jehucal%20son%20of%20Shelemiah%2C%20and%20Zephaniah%20the%20priest%2C%20son%20of%20Maaseiah%2C%20to%20ask%20Jeremiah%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BPlease%20pray%20to%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20our%20God%20for%20us.%26%23x201D%3B%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_37_4%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2237%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EJeremiah%20had%20not%20yet%20been%20imprisoned%2C%20so%20he%20could%20come%20and%20go%20among%20the%20people%20as%20he%20pleased.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_37_5%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2237%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EAt%20this%20time%20the%20army%20of%20Pharaoh%20Hophra%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E37%3A5a%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Earmy%20of%20Pharaoh%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%20see%2044%3A30.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20of%20Egypt%20appeared%20at%20the%20southern%20border%20of%20Judah.%20When%20the%20Babylonian%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E37%3A5b%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Or%20%3Cem%3EChaldean%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%20also%20in%2037%3A10%2C%2011.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20army%20heard%20about%20it%2C%20they%20withdrew%20from%20their%20siege%20of%20Jerusalem.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_37_6%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2237%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20gave%20this%20message%20to%20Jeremiah%3A%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_37_7%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2237%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BThis%20is%20what%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20the%20God%20of%20Israel%2C%20says%3A%20The%20king%20of%20Judah%20sent%20you%20to%20ask%20me%20what%20is%20going%20to%20happen.%20Tell%20him%2C%20%26%23x2018%3BPharaoh%26%23x2019%3Bs%20army%20is%20about%20to%20return%20to%20Egypt%2C%20though%20he%20came%20here%20to%20help%20you.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_37_8%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2237%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20the%20Babylonians%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E37%3A8%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Or%20%3Cem%3EChaldeans%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%20also%20in%2037%3A9%2C%2013.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20will%20come%20back%20and%20capture%20this%20city%20and%20burn%20it%20to%20the%20ground.%26%23x2019%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_37_9%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2237%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BThis%20is%20what%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20says%3A%20Do%20not%20fool%20yourselves%20into%20thinking%20that%20the%20Babylonians%20are%20gone%20for%20good.%20They%20aren%26%23x2019%3Bt!%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_37_10%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2237%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3EEven%20if%20you%20were%20to%20destroy%20the%20entire%20Babylonian%20army%2C%20leaving%20only%20a%20handful%20of%20wounded%20survivors%2C%20they%20would%20still%20stagger%20from%20their%20tents%20and%20burn%20this%20city%20to%20the%20ground!%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_37_11%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2237%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EJeremiah%20Is%20Imprisoned%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20the%20Babylonian%20army%20left%20Jerusalem%20because%20of%20Pharaoh%26%23x2019%3Bs%20approaching%20army%2C%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_37_12%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2237%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3EJeremiah%20started%20to%20leave%20the%20city%20on%20his%20way%20to%20the%20territory%20of%20Benjamin%2C%20to%20claim%20his%20share%20of%20the%20property%20among%20his%20relatives%20there.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E37%3A12%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Eto%20separate%20from%20there%20in%20the%20midst%20of%20the%20people.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_37_13%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2237%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20as%20he%20was%20walking%20through%20the%20Benjamin%20Gate%2C%20a%20sentry%20arrested%20him%20and%20said%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BYou%20are%20defecting%20to%20the%20Babylonians!%26%23x201D%3B%20The%20sentry%20making%20the%20arrest%20was%20Irijah%20son%20of%20Shelemiah%2C%20grandson%20of%20Hananiah.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_37_14%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2237%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BThat%26%23x2019%3Bs%20not%20true!%26%23x201D%3B%20Jeremiah%20protested.%20%26%23x201C%3BI%20had%20no%20intention%20of%20doing%20any%20such%20thing.%26%23x201D%3B%20But%20Irijah%20wouldn%26%23x2019%3Bt%20listen%2C%20and%20he%20took%20Jeremiah%20before%20the%20officials.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_37_15%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2237%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3EThey%20were%20furious%20with%20Jeremiah%20and%20had%20him%20flogged%20and%20imprisoned%20in%20the%20house%20of%20Jonathan%20the%20secretary.%20Jonathan%26%23x2019%3Bs%20house%20had%20been%20converted%20into%20a%20prison.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_37_16%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2237%22%20vn%3D%2216%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3EJeremiah%20was%20put%20into%20a%20dungeon%20cell%2C%20where%20he%20remained%20for%20many%20days.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_37_17%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2237%22%20vn%3D%2217%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E17%3C%2Fspan%3ELater%20King%20Zedekiah%20secretly%20requested%20that%20Jeremiah%20come%20to%20the%20palace%2C%20where%20the%20king%20asked%20him%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BDo%20you%20have%20any%20messages%20from%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%3F%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%26%23x201C%3BYes%2C%20I%20do!%26%23x201D%3B%20said%20Jeremiah.%20%26%23x201C%3BYou%20will%20be%20defeated%20by%20the%20king%20of%20Babylon.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_37_18%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2237%22%20vn%3D%2218%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E18%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20Jeremiah%20asked%20the%20king%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BWhat%20crime%20have%20I%20committed%3F%20What%20have%20I%20done%20against%20you%2C%20your%20attendants%2C%20or%20the%20people%20that%20I%20should%20be%20imprisoned%20like%20this%3F%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_37_19%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2237%22%20vn%3D%2219%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E19%3C%2Fspan%3EWhere%20are%20your%20prophets%20now%20who%20told%20you%20the%20king%20of%20Babylon%20would%20not%20attack%20you%20or%20this%20land%3F%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_37_20%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2237%22%20vn%3D%2220%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E20%3C%2Fspan%3EListen%2C%20my%20lord%20the%20king%2C%20I%20beg%20you.%20Don%26%23x2019%3Bt%20send%20me%20back%20to%20the%20dungeon%20in%20the%20house%20of%20Jonathan%20the%20secretary%2C%20for%20I%20will%20die%20there.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_37_21%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2237%22%20vn%3D%2221%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E21%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20King%20Zedekiah%20commanded%20that%20Jeremiah%20not%20be%20returned%20to%20the%20dungeon.%20Instead%2C%20he%20was%20imprisoned%20in%20the%20courtyard%20of%20the%20guard%20in%20the%20royal%20palace.%20The%20king%20also%20commanded%20that%20Jeremiah%20be%20given%20a%20loaf%20of%20fresh%20bread%20every%20day%20as%20long%20as%20there%20was%20any%20left%20in%20the%20city.%20So%20Jeremiah%20was%20put%20in%20the%20palace%20prison.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_38_1%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2238%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3EJeremiah%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E38%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EJeremiah%20in%20a%20Cistern%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3ENow%20Shephatiah%20son%20of%20Mattan%2C%20Gedaliah%20son%20of%20Pashhur%2C%20Jehucal%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E38%3A1%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3EJucal%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20a%20variant%20spelling%20of%20Jehucal%3B%20see%2037%3A3.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20son%20of%20Shelemiah%2C%20and%20Pashhur%20son%20of%20Malkijah%20heard%20what%20Jeremiah%20had%20been%20telling%20the%20people.%20He%20had%20been%20saying%2C%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_38_2%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2238%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BThis%20is%20what%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20says%3A%20%26%23x2018%3BEveryone%20who%20stays%20in%20Jerusalem%20will%20die%20from%20war%2C%20famine%2C%20or%20disease%2C%20but%20those%20who%20surrender%20to%20the%20Babylonians%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E38%3A2%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Or%20%3Cem%3EChaldeans%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%20also%20in%2038%3A18%2C%2019%2C%2023.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20will%20l